issue.title: Please validate TF converter with ORT 1.12 release candidate

repository.name: tensorflow-onnx
repository.description: Convert TensorFlow, Keras, Tensorflow.js and Tflite models to ONNX

body:
@skottmckay , could you please help take a look at this issue? It looks like same issue as https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/12099.

We also need to handle axis.

Did this test pass with the previous version of ORT? 

The axis should be handled by https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/178a413ca1ae74c3b7c70ee6c07fb86ead61b3c1/onnxruntime/core/optimizer/transpose_optimizer/transpose_optimizer.cc#L1219

but maybe we're missing a step of updating the attribute in the 'real' node.

Currently we're using the same perms for both HandleQuantizeDequantizeScale and TransposeFirstInput in the second pass.

https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/178a413ca1ae74c3b7c70ee6c07fb86ead61b3c1/onnxruntime/core/optimizer/transpose_optimizer/transpose_optimizer.cc#L2000-L2004

Looks like the axis needs to be inverted when calling HandleQuantizeDequantizeScale. That would match the behavior here where TransposeFirstInput and HandleQuantizeDequantizeScale are called.

https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/178a413ca1ae74c3b7c70ee6c07fb86ead61b3c1/onnxruntime/core/optimizer/transpose_optimizer/transpose_optimizer.cc#L1225-L1230

> Did this test pass with the previous version of ORT?
> 
> The axis should be handled by
> 
> https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/178a413ca1ae74c3b7c70ee6c07fb86ead61b3c1/onnxruntime/core/optimizer/transpose_optimizer/transpose_optimizer.cc#L1219
> 
> but maybe we're missing a step of updating the attribute in the 'real' node.

Yes, it passed with the previous version of ORT 1.11.1.

issue.title: Fix GH issue 12151 by using inverse perms for updating DQ axis attribute

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 
Need to use inverse perms for updating that axis to what is used for transposing the input. This only applies if the DQ node is doing per-axis dequantization.

**Motivation and Context**
#12151

body:
The issue has gone, so close it.
Thanks!
